title: Toyota at top in global vehicle sales - Yahoo7 Finance Australia
text:
Related Content View Photo 

Toyota remains the top carmaker in global vehicle sales after the first nine months of this year, outpacing rivals General Motors and Volkswagen.
Toyota has announced that global sales for the first three quarters totalled 7.498 million vehicles.
Volkswagen sold 7.43 million vehicles, while GM sold 7.2 million vehicles, according to their figures released earlier this month.
Detroit-based GM was the top-selling carmaker for more than seven decades until being surpassed by Toyota in 2008.
GM retook the sales crown for one year in 2011, when a tsunami and quake disaster struck Japan, disrupting production.
Toyota made a big comeback in 2012, and has been the top automaker for the past three years.
Last year, Toyota, which makes the Prius hybrid, Camry sedan and Lexus luxury models, sold 10.23 million vehicles.
